==Maori and New Zealand English==
===Alternative spellings===
* Aotearoa New Zealand 
===Etymology===
:From [[Maori]]: literal translation - Land of the Long White Cloud (''ao'' = cloud, ''tea'' = white, ''roa'' = long). A reference to the appearance of mountanous land when seen on the horizon from a canoe after an ocean voyage.

===Proper Noun===
#The country of [[New Zealand]].
